# Niagara System: Campfire Survival Tool
# Central survival mechanic — warmth, cooking, light, safety

## EMITTER 1: Fire Core
- Spawn Rate: 200-400 particles/second
- Lifetime: 1.0-2.5 seconds
- Size: 0.3-1.5 world units
- Velocity: Strong upward (3-8 m/s) with random spread
- Color: Fire gradient (255,100,0) to (255,255,100) to (100,100,100)
- Material: M_Fire_Additive

### Behavior Modules:
- Initial Location: Fire pit center with radial spread
- Velocity: Upward with turbulence noise
- Color Over Life: Hot orange → bright yellow → smoke gray
- Size Over Life: Growth then shrinkage
- Curl Noise: Realistic fire movement
- Wind Interaction: Directional influence from weather

### Fuel System Integration:
- Wood_Quality_Parameter: Affects burn intensity and color
- Fuel_Level: Controls spawn rate and lifetime
- Oxygen_Level: Wind affects combustion efficiency

## EMITTER 2: Smoke Column
- Spawn Rate: 50-100 particles/second
- Lifetime: 8-15 seconds
- Size: 1.0-4.0 world units (expanding over time)
- Velocity: Upward with wind drift
- Color: Dark gray (80,80,80) fading to transparent
- Material: M_Smoke_Volumetric

### Behavior Modules:
- Initial Location: Above fire core
- Velocity: Upward with strong wind influence
- Size Over Life: Continuous expansion
- Color Over Life: Dark to transparent fade
- Collision: Disperses on contact with objects
- Weather Response: Rain disperses smoke faster

### Visibility Mechanics:
- Smoke_Visibility_Range: 200-500 meters
- Predator_Attraction: Smoke can attract curious dinosaurs
- Wind_Dispersion: Strong wind reduces visibility range

## EMITTER 3: Ember Sparks
- Spawn Rate: 20-50 particles/second (bursts during wood cracking)
- Lifetime: 0.5-2.0 seconds
- Size: 0.1-0.3 world units
- Velocity: Random upward arcs
- Color: Bright orange-red (255,150,50)
- Material: M_Ember_Additive

### Behavior Modules:
- Initial Location: Fire edges with random distribution
- Velocity: Ballistic arcs with gravity
- Color Over Life: Bright to dark fade
- Collision: Bounce on ground, extinguish in water
- Audio Trigger: Crackling sound events

### Safety Mechanics:
- Grass_Ignition_Risk: Embers can start small fires
- Player_Burn_Damage: Contact causes damage
- Rain_Extinguish: Water immediately kills embers

## EMITTER 4: Heat Distortion
- Spawn Rate: 100 particles/second
- Lifetime: 1.0 seconds
- Size: 2.0-5.0 world units
- Velocity: Upward thermal column
- Color: Invisible (used for distortion only)
- Material: M_HeatDistortion_Refraction

### Behavior Modules:
- Initial Location: Above fire with cylindrical volume
- Velocity: Thermal updraft simulation
- Refraction Strength: Heat-based distortion intensity
- Temperature Zones: Stronger effect closer to fire

## EMITTER 5: Cooking Steam (When Food Present)
- Spawn Rate: 30-60 particles/second
- Lifetime: 3-5 seconds
- Size: 0.5-1.5 world units
- Velocity: Upward with slight spread
- Color: White-gray (240,240,240)
- Material: M_CookingSteam_Translucent

### Behavior Modules:
- Initial Location: Cooking surface positions
- Food Type Response: Different effects for meat/vegetables
- Cooking Progress: Intensity increases with cooking time
- Aroma Simulation: Particle trails suggest food smells

## SYSTEM PARAMETERS:
- Fire_Intensity: 0.0-2.0 (controls all emission rates)
- Wind_Strength: 0.0-3.0 (affects smoke and flame direction)
- Fuel_Type: Enum (dry wood, green wood, special materials)
- Weather_Condition: Rain/snow affects fire behavior
- Cooking_Active: Boolean (enables cooking steam emitter)